cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.GR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on image processing and computer vision techniques, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of filtering techniques and image zooming also suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of information theory and signal processing techniques, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of edge preservation techniques and image enhancement could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category. Finally, the use of image processing techniques for medical applications could suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
